# React Flow -- Layout, Grouping, and Validation Patterns

## Auto Layout

### Dagre (Simple Tree/DAG Layout)

```bash
npm install @dagrejs/dagre
```

Use `Dagre.layout()` to compute positions, then update nodes.

### ELK (Advanced Layout)

```bash
npm install elkjs
```

Use `elk.layout()` for more advanced layout algorithms.

## Sub-Flows & Grouping

Use `parentId` and `extent: "parent"` for child nodes. Group nodes must appear BEFORE children in the nodes array. Set explicit dimensions on group nodes.

## Connection Validation

Prevent self-connections and cycles using `isValidConnection`. Use `getOutgoers` for DFS cycle detection. Limit connections per handle with `useHandleConnections`.

## Drag and Drop Sidebar

Set `application/reactflow` data on drag start, use `screenToFlowPosition` on drop to place nodes at the correct canvas position.

