# React Flow -- Persistence, Theming, Testing, and Collaboration

## Keyboard Shortcuts

Use `useKeyPress` for copy/paste/cut/undo/redo/fitView bindings.

## Flow Serialization

Use `toObject()` from `useReactFlow` to serialize. Restore with `setNodes`, `setEdges`, `setViewport`.

## Theming

Override React Flow CSS variables in your globals.css:

```css
.react-flow {
  --xy-background-color: theme("colors.background");
  --xy-edge-stroke: theme("colors.border");
  --xy-node-background-color: theme("colors.card");
  /* ... */
}
```

## Performance for Large Flows (500+ nodes)

1. Memo everything
2. Define nodeTypes/edgeTypes outside component
3. useCallback all handlers
4. Use useStore selectors, not useNodes/useEdges
5. Batch updates in single set() calls

## Testing

Mock `ResizeObserver` in tests. Wrap components in `ReactFlowProvider`. Use `data-id` attributes for node selection.

## Multiplayer

Use `onNodesChange`/`onEdgesChange` to broadcast and apply remote changes via WebSocket/CRDT. Consider Yjs or Liveblocks for production.

## SSR

Pre-define `width` and `height` on nodes for server-side rendering support.
